org.apache.ignite.visor.plugin

Interface VisorPluginModel


  • public interface VisorPluginModel
    Gateway to Visor functionality from plugins. Plugins will receive model instance from Visor, usually passed into constructor, e.g. VisorExtensionPoint.VisorExtensionPoint(VisorPluginModel).

      • execute

        <A,R> R execute(Class<? extends ComputeTask<A,R>> taskCls,
              Collection<UUID> nodeIds,
              @Nullable
              A arg)
          throws IllegalStateException
        Executes given task on this grid projection. For step-by-step explanation of task execution process refer to ComputeTask documentation.
        Type Parameters:
        A - Argument type.
        R - Result type.
        Parameters:
        taskCls - Class of the task to execute. If class has ComputeTaskName annotation, then task is deployed under a name specified within annotation. Otherwise, full class name is used as task name.
        nodeIds - Node IDs on with execute task.
        arg - Optional argument of task execution, can be null.
        Returns:
        Task result.
        Throws:
        IllegalStateException - If Visor not connected to the grid.

      • execute

        <A,R> R execute(String taskName,
              Collection<UUID> nodeIds,
              @Nullable
              A arg)
          throws IllegalStateException
        Executes given task on this grid projection. For step-by-step explanation of task execution process refer to ComputeTask documentation.
        Type Parameters:
        A - Argument type.
        R - Result type.
        Parameters:
        taskName - Name of the task to execute.
        nodeIds - Node IDs on with execute task.
        arg - Optional argument of task execution, can be null.
        Returns:
        Task result.
        Throws:
        IllegalStateException - If Visor not connected to the grid.
